  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>The Giant
  Kaltor is a large invertebrate crustacean with many arachnid features.<o:=
p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>They
  typically inhabit the upper atmosphere of Frozen Gas Giant planets, but t=
hey roam
  freely through space and thus can be found nearly anywhere in a system.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>They are
  also often found at Gas Clouds throughout the galaxy. How they arrived at
  these isolated locations is unknown.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Kaltors
  are very aggressive and territorial &#8211; they will attack any approach=
ing
  ships. They are quite fast-moving and very agile. Their attack is swift a=
nd
  merciless: they eat any ships they can catch.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Shielding
  is useless against these creatures &#8211; they munch straight through
  shields, destroying the ship&#8217;s components.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Unless
  you have overwhelming force, it is wise to steer clear of Giant Kaltors.<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>
